            <h4 style="color:black;">Using Circles in Contexts</h4>
            <p>Sometimes young children encounter mathematical contexts requiring them to partition a circle, such as analogue clocks and circle graphs. Accurately equi-partitioning the area of a circle requires students to conceptually understand the area of a circle, something not introduced until intermediate grades. When students don’t understand the area of a circle, they may partition the circle like this:</p>
