                                    <img src="/images/research/supportDocs/RectanglesNumberLinesCircles/recNumLinesCircle-11.jpg"  class="img-responsive margin-auto" />
                                </figure>
                                <p>This student used an area model to respond to the prompt “Identify some fractions that have a sum equal to 1”.They flexibly represent addition with unlike denominators. Notice the use of colour to represent the combined fractions as a sum of <abbr title="four eighths" class="abbr-frac"><span class="frac"><sup>4</sup><span>&frasl;</span><sub>8</sub></span></abbr> + <abbr title="two fourths" class="abbr-frac"><span class="frac"><sup>2</sup><span>&frasl;</span><sub>4</sub></span></abbr> = 1. In addition to colour, the student’s effective use of grid paper highlights the equivalent relationships.</p>
